Elgeyo Marakwet assembly speaker Albert Kochei (pictured) wants Parliament to pass a law barring doctors and nurses from going on strike, just as the police and military are not allowed.Medics began their strike on December 5.On Friday last week, Kochei said the law would prevent many lives being lost during medics&rsquo; strike. &ldquo;I believe we shall have a Bill to ensure doctors and nurses don&rsquo;t go on strike,&rdquo; he said.Kochei said medics&rsquo; code of ethics does not allow them to ignore patients. &ldquo;We have witnessed doctors and nurses refusing to attend to critically ill patients during their strike,&rdquo; he said.